Requirement Specification — Auto-parts Marketplace & Vendor Dispatch App
1. Overview
Purpose: Build a lightweight cross-platform (iOS, Android, Windows) mobile app + admin web/desktop console that allows customers to browse and order auto-parts, vendors to accept & dispatch orders, and admin to manage inventory, vendors, payments and analytics. UI/UX should be inspired by Boodmo (clean catalog, parts categories, cart, vendor assignment flows) but not copied.
Primary actors
•
Admin — full platform control (inventory, vendors, orders, payments, dashboard).
•
Customer — browses, orders parts, pays, tracks history, chats with vendor.
•
Vendor — registers store, receives nearby orders, accepts & dispatches, views own history.
•
Payment Gateway / Bank — handles payments to admin’s account.
•
System — notification, geolocation, matching engine, central DB, chat & realtime.
2. High-level Functional Requirements
2.1 Admin (Console / App)
•
FR-A1: Admin can upload inventory items (part name, SKU/part number, brand, category, sub-category, description, images, price, tax, service time / lead time, stock count, unit type: pcs|box|carton).
•
FR-A2: Admin can bulk upload (CSV/XLSX) and bulk edit inventory.
•
FR-A3: Admin can add/modify/delete vendors. Vendor profile includes store name, owner name, contact details, store address, store location coordinates (lat/long), pin code, service areas, bank details (for KYC), status (pending, approved, blocked).
•
FR-A4: Admin can moderate vendor registrations (approve/reject) and add notes/required documents. Only approved vendors are active.
•
FR-A5: Admin can view all customers’ orders and manually assign orders to vendors by proximity, or allow automatic assignment (configurable).
