7. Realtime / Concurrency Details (Critical)
•
Use atomic locking when vendor accepts an order (Redis SETNX or DB transaction with WHERE vendor_id IS NULL update). This ensures "first-accept-wins".
•
After assignment, broadcast update to all connected vendors so order is removed.
