•
For occasional race conditions, server must check assignment again before confirming to vendor and return appropriate status to losing vendors.
8. Chat & Messaging
•
Lightweight in-app chat per order; messages stored in DB with attachments in object storage.
•
Use WebSocket for immediate delivery, fallback to push notifications.
•
Allow vendor/customer to see chat history only for orders they are part of.
9. Payment Flow & Bank Management
•
Integrate with a PCI-compliant Payment Gateway (gateway handles card details). Support UPI, netbanking, cards, wallets.
•
Admin console to configure gateway credentials, webhook URL, settlement account (bank).
•
Record all transactions, webhooks must be idempotent (use gateway txn id).
•
Provide refunds via gateway APIs; admin triggers refund flow.
10. Admin Dashboard Features
•
Real-time KPIs: Today’s orders, pending assignments, completed, cancellations, revenue, app downloads (from stores), active vendors & customers.
•
Filters by date range, vendor, category, city/pincode.
•
Inventory alerts (low stock), automatic reorder suggestions.
•
Export transactions / invoices / vendor statements.
11. Security & Compliance
•
OTP verification, strong JWT tokens, refresh tokens with secure storage.
•
All APIs behind TLS. Secure headers (CSP, HSTS).
•
Role-based access control: admin vs vendor vs customer.
•
Input validation and rate limiting to prevent abuse.
•
If storing PII or operating in India, follow local data protection regulations and best practices.
